This presidential memorandum, issued on December 10, 2020 by Donald J. Trump, provides an order of succession within the Office of Personnel Management (OPM). According to the memorandum, in the event that both the Director and Deputy Director of OPM are unable to perform their duties, the following officials will act as and perform the functions of the Director: Chief of Staff, General Counsel, Associate Director of Employee Services, Chief Management Officer, Chief Financial Officer, Associate Director of Retirement Services, and other Associate Directors in the order of their appointment. The memorandum also includes exceptions, stating that individuals serving in an acting capacity in any of the listed positions cannot act as the Director, and the President has the discretion to depart from this order if permitted by law. Additionally, a previous memorandum from August 12, 2016, designating officers of the OPM to act as Director, is revoked. The memorandum concludes with general provisions, stating that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits and authorizes publication in the Federal Register.